name: Tonto Yer
description:
He was the orange complementing my purple, fire complementing magic. 
We were worlds apart yet somehow found each other right before the world fell apart, as the coronavirus took over. 

Each element on the right represents a memory from our brief time together; 
The last remnants of a different world experienced by two people different to the world, same to each other. 

This piece is a tribute to Tonto Yer by his Tata So, brought together by the pandemic but also torn apart by it. 

*At the time of minting, we remain friends still separated by seas and fate. 

2000 x 2000 px
